cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SD, cs.NE 

The paper deals with clustering and community detection in large scale complex networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of kernel spectral clustering and the focus on real-life networks suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of internal cluster quality metrics suggests cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the study of network structure and organization is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
